PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F445A1775927152
OL,3,CRory McIlroy plans to keep his foot on
OL,4,Cthe gas after surging clear at Augusta
OL,6,FHis brilliant approach, trickling down
OL,7,Fthe slope to three feet at the 16th,
OL,8,Fput a third two on his card and he
OL,9,Fcould seemingly do no wrong as, having
OL,10,Fpunched out from under the trees, he
OL,11,Fchipped in at the next.
OL,13,FAs if to underline his dominance he
OL,14,Fstruck his approach to the last to six
OL,15,Ffeet for a ninth birdie of the day.
OL,17,FReed had to settle for a second-
OL,18,Fsuccessive 69 after dropping his only
OL,19,Fshot at the 18th, which meant he
OL,20,Fmissed out on a third-round final
OL,21,Fpairing with McIlroy.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/9
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
